## Column Selection Guidelines
1. Choose column(s) containing the data the model needs to perform the task
2. EXCLUDE meaningless columns: IDs, UUIDs, timestamps, row numbers, internal identifiers
3. PREFER columns with: text content, questions, documents, or structured data relevant to the task
4. If multiple columns are needed (e.g., "title" + "body"), list them comma-separated

## Format Definitions
- single_turn: Simple request/response pairs (questions, single prompts)
- multi_turn: Conversational data with multiple exchanges (chat history, dialogues)
- document: Long-form text for processing (articles, documents, reports)
- structured: Structured records or JSON data (forms, database rows, API responses)

## Examples
- Customer questions column → source_column: "question", format: "single_turn"
- Chat history with messages → source_column: "messages", format: "multi_turn"
- Article text for summarization → source_column: "content", format: "document"
- Support ticket with title and description → source_column: "title, description", format: "single_turn"

Return JSON:
